# Design System

## Brand palette

| Token          | Hex       | Usage                              |
|----------------|-----------|------------------------------------|
| `midnight`     | `#0b1d3a` | Dark backgrounds, primary dark     |
| `deep-navy`    | `#132d5e` | Gradient endpoints                 |
| `gold`         | `#c9a96e` | Primary accent, CTAs, eyebrows     |
| `gold-light`   | `#d4bc8a` | Hover states                       |
| `teal`         | `#1a5c5e` | Secondary accent                   |
| `off-white`    | `#f8f6f2` | Cream backgrounds                  |
| `charcoal`     | `#2a2a2a` | Body text on light backgrounds     |

Use Tailwind classes: `bg-midnight`, `text-gold`, `bg-off-white`, etc. (mapped via `@theme inline` in `global.css`).

## Typography

- **Headings**: `font-serif` (Playfair Display) — all `<h1>`–`<h4>` inherit this
- **Body**: `font-sans` (Inter Variable)
- **Eyebrow**: 11px, 700 weight, `0.24em` letter-spacing, uppercase, gold color — use `.eyebrow` class
- **Section titles**: use `.section-title` (responsive clamp 32px–52px)
- **Subtitles**: use `.section-subtitle` (18px, light weight, mid-gray)

## Spacing tokens

Use `var(--space-*)` or Tailwind `spacing-*` (xs=8, sm=16, md=24, lg=48, xl=80, 2xl=120, 3xl=160).

Layout containers: `.pp-container` (max 1280px) and `.pp-container-narrow` (max 720px).
Section padding: `.pp-section` or `.pp-section-tight`.

## Module theme system

Every module section has a `theme` field in Sanity: `"dark"`, `"white"`, or `"cream"`.

Apply via `data-theme` attribute on the section wrapper:

```tsx
<section data-theme={theme} style={{ background: "var(--section-bg)" }}>
```

CSS variables set per theme: `--section-bg`, `--section-text`, `--section-muted`, `--section-accent`.
Dark theme overrides `.section-title` to white and `em` to gold.

## Button hierarchy

1. **Primary CTA**: `Button variant="brand" size="cta"` — gold bg (`bg-gold`), **white** text, **rectangular** (`rounded`, 4px radius), 13px/600/uppercase/1px tracking, hover: lift + gold shadow
2. **Secondary CTA**: `Button variant="outline" size="cta"` — transparent bg, midnight text, `border-warm-gray`, same font treatment, hover: border darkens to midnight
3. **In-page secondary**: `.btn-secondary` — text-only, white/60 opacity, uppercase (used inline in hero, not a Button component)
4. **Nav CTA**: `Button variant="nav"` — gold border pill, transparent bg, gold text (pill shape is intentional for nav only)

### Key button rules
- **Never** use `variant="brand"` with `rounded-full` — the brand CTA is rectangular per the design spec
- **Never** use `text-midnight` or `text-primary-foreground` on `variant="brand"` — it must be `text-white`
- Always pair `variant="brand"` or `variant="outline"` with `size="cta"` for page-level CTAs
- The `nav` variant is the only pill-shaped button; all others are rectangular

## shadcn usage

- Install: `npx shadcn@latest add <component>`
- Config: `components.json` (style: `radix-vega`, aliases under `@/`)
- Installed: `button`, `card`, `badge`, `avatar`, `sheet`, `navigation-menu`
- Button has custom variants: `brand`, `nav`, `outline` (CTA-style) and size `cta`

## Animation

- `.reveal` / `.reveal-left` / `.reveal-right` + `.visible` for scroll-triggered entrance
- `.reveal-delay-{1..4}` for staggered children
- `RevealObserver` component handles intersection detection
